{
  "answer": "**Mirza Ghalib's famous opening couplet (sher) from his ghazal in *Diwan-e-Ghalib* (Ghazal #84):**\n\n**Original (Urdu):**  \nعشق مجھ کو نہیں وحشت ہی سہی  \nمیری وحشت تری شہرت ہی سہی[^1]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nIshq mujh ko nahin vehshat hi sahi  \nMeri vehshat teri shohrat hi sahi[^2]\n\n**Translation:**  \nIf not your love, this wild obsession—so be it;  \nMy obsession only builds your fame—then so be it.[^3]\n\nThis defiant matla expresses resignation to unrequited love, preferring even madness (*vehshat/wahshat*) over nothing, as it at least enhances the beloved's renown. The full ghazal continues this theme across ten couplets.[^4]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/84-ishq-mujh-ko-nahin-vehshat-hi-sahi/original/#p-c00f68).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/84-ishq-mujh-ko-nahin-vehshat-hi-sahi/transliteration/#p-d32e8b).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/84-ishq-mujh-ko-nahin-vehshat-hi-sahi/translation/#p-a4c81f).\n\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/84-ishq-mujh-ko-nahin-vehshat-hi-sahi/translation/).",
